# Traceability (RULE-007, RULE-008)

## Product docs and HLD

- Keep PRD, architecture intent, and HLD under the **conventional** paths **`docs/prd/`**, **`docs/architecture/`**, and **`docs/design/`** when your program uses a `docs/` tree (filenames are project-specific). See **`.kfs/agent/START.md`** and **`.kfs/INDEX.md`**; HLD **structure and trace** expectations: **`.kfs/specs/design_spec.md`**.
- **Change log or version history (end of file):** When those folders exist, every **`*.md`** under **`docs/prd/`**, **`docs/architecture/`**, **`docs/design/`**, and **`docs/test/`** must **end** with **`## Change log`** or **`## Version history`** (table: **revision**, **date** (`last_updated`), **status**, **supersedes**, **what changed**) per **`.kfs/specs/prd_spec.md`** and **`.kfs/specs/design_spec.md`**. Agents creating or editing these files must **add or refresh** that section on merge.
- Optional **operational** depth: test strategy, infrastructure, and CI/CD in **`.kfs/specs/test_strategy_spec.md`**, **`.kfs/specs/infrastructure_spec.md`**, **`.kfs/specs/cicd_spec.md`**; architecture intent and HLD should **link** to these instead of duplicating long runbooks.
- They MUST remain **consistent** with indexed primitives under `knowledge/` (no contradictory “source of truth” in prose).
- **Release-by-release** — When PRD, HLD, or **`docs/test/`** plans change across trains, keep **trace links** current: driving **`FEAT-*`**, accurate **`CONR-*`** versioning for published surfaces, and doc **metadata** (`status`, **`superseded`**, `last_updated`) per **`.kfs/specs/prd_spec.md`** and **`.kfs/specs/design_spec.md`**.

Typed relationship vocabulary (guides, uses, derived_from, enforces, verifies, implements, constrains, references): **`.kfs/specs/knowledge_model_spec.md`** §7–8 — use when describing or validating trace links in reviews or knowledge design.

Sequencing when architecture or scope changes (knowledge vs docs PRs): **`.cursor/skills/merge-knowledge-first/SKILL.md`**.

## End-to-end traceability

- **Spec → primitives** — FEAT files reference real CON/INV/DEC/CONR IDs in `catalog.yml`.
- **HLD/PRD → primitives** — Major sections trace to FEAT and/or specific CON/INV as the team has established.
- **Code → spec** — Features and behavioral changes should be attributable to a FEAT (or an explicit tech task that still respects CON/INV/CONR).
- **Tests → invariants (and constraints)** — Tests should be nameable or comment-linked to INV/CON IDs where practical.

If trace breaks, fix the **knowledge graph or catalog** first, then code/docs — not the other way around.
